@page "/"

<PageTitle>Jay's Portfolio</PageTitle>

<style>
    /* Visual Studio Code Dark+ Palette Overrides */
    .vs-keyword {
        color: #569CD6 !important;
    }
    /* IDE Blue (Keywords like public, class) */
    .vs-type {
        color: #4EC9B0 !important;
    }
    /* IDE Teal (Classes, Interfaces, Types) */
    .vs-text {
        color: #C586C0 !important;
    }
    /* IDE Purple/Pink (Control flow keywords like if, return, switch) */
    .vs-comment {
        color: #6A9955 !important;
    }
    /* IDE Green (Comments and documentation) */
    .vs-string {
        color: #CE9178 !important;
    }
    /* IDE Terracotta/Orange (Strings & Values) */
    .vs-accent-line {
        border-color: #569CD6 !important;
    }
    /* Blue vertical accent timeline */

    /* Clean formatting for the inline code elements */
    .vs-code-inline {
        background-color: #2D2D2D !important;
        color: #CE9178 !important;
        padding: 2px 6px;
        border-radius: 4px;
        font-family: monospace;
    }

    /* Soften the bootstrap horizontal rules to match the dark environment */
    .vs-hr {
        border-color: #333333 !important;
        opacity: 0.4;
    }

    /* IDE Interactive Toggle (Details/Summary) Styling */
    .vs-toggle {
        display: block;
    }

        .vs-toggle summary {
            cursor: pointer;
            list-style: none; /* Removes default browser arrow */
            outline: none;
            user-select: none;
        }

            /* Hide default arrow for WebKit/Safari browsers */
            .vs-toggle summary::-webkit-details-marker {
                display: none;
            }

            /* Custom VS Code style folding arrow indicator */
            .vs-toggle summary::before {
                content: "▶";
                color: #858585;
                display: inline-block;
                margin-right: 12px;
                font-size: 0.95rem;
                transition: transform 0.1s ease;
                vertical-align: middle;
            }

        /* Rotate the indicator arrow when the code block is expanded/open */
        .vs-toggle[open] summary::before {
            transform: rotate(90deg);
            color: #569CD6; /* Turns IDE Blue when active */
        }

    /* Keep heading baseline aligned with the toggle arrow */
    .vs-toggle-heading {
        display: inline-block;
        vertical-align: middle;
    }
</style>

<div class="container max-width-md my-5 py-3">

    <header class="mb-5">
        <h1 class="h3 fw-bold text-uppercase tracking-wider vs-keyword mb-4">About Me</h1>

        <p class="lead vs-text fs-4 lh-lg m-0">
            Hi, my name is <span class="vs-type fw-bold text-nowrap">Jay Panchal</span>.
            I'm a <span class="vs-string fw-bold">software developer</span> specializing in robust backend systems,
            complex data transformation pipelines, and automation tools. I bring four years of professional
            experience writing clean, deterministic, and maintainable code.
        </p>
    </header>

    <hr class="vs-hr my-5" />

    <section class="mb-5">
        <details class="vs-toggle" open>
            <summary>
                <h2 class="h3 fw-bold text-uppercase tracking-wider vs-keyword m-0 vs-toggle-heading">Core Expertise</h2>
            </summary>

            <div class="row mt-5">
                <div class="col-md-6 mb-4">
                    <h3 class="h6 text-uppercase vs-comment fw-bold font-monospace mb-2">// Languages & Frameworks</h3>
                    <p class="vs-text fs-5">C#, .NET Core, Blazor WebAssembly, Perl</p>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-6 mb-4">
                    <h3 class="h6 text-uppercase vs-comment fw-bold font-monospace mb-2">// Data & Automation</h3>
                    <p class="vs-text fs-5">XML, XSLT, Content Transformation, Scripting</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </details>
    </section>

    <hr class="vs-hr my-5" />

    <section class="mb-5">
        <details class="vs-toggle" open>
            <summary>
                <h2 class="h3 fw-bold text-uppercase tracking-wider vs-keyword m-0 vs-toggle-heading">Selected Projects</h2>
            </summary>

            <div class="mt-5">
                <div class="project-entry mb-5 border-start border-2 vs-accent-line ps-4">
                    <div class="d-flex justify-content-between align-items-baseline flex-wrap mb-2">
                        <h3 class="h4 fw-bold m-0 vs-type">aDocs — Enterprise Document Processing Pipeline</h3>
                        <span class="vs-comment font-monospace small">// C# • XML • XSLT • Perl • Core Automation</span>
                    </div>

                    <p class="vs-text my-3 lh-lg">
                        An automated, high-volume data ingestion engine designed to process transactional banking statements (PDF/AFP formats) and synthesize them into specialized, legally compliant accessibility distributions like Large Print, Braille, and tagged PDFs.
                    </p>

                    <div class="row pt-2">
                        <div class="col-md-6 mb-3">
                            <h4 class="h6 text-uppercase fw-bold vs-keyword small tracking-wide mb-2">The Architecture</h4>
                            <p class="vs-text small lh-base">
                                Extracts text from binary print streams into raw XML, executes multi-stage XSLT sanitization filters (<code class="vs-code-inline">xmlorig</code>), and uses a custom schema orchestrator (<code class="vs-code-inline">model.xml</code>) with regex-pattern matching to dynamically map layout structures.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-md-6 mb-3">
                            <h4 class="h6 text-uppercase fw-bold vs-keyword small tracking-wide mb-2">Engineering Win</h4>
                            <p class="vs-text small lh-base">
                                Diagnosed a critical throughput race condition via runtime execution logs. Refactored script orchestration to guarantee pre-filters trigger only post-file generation, restoring absolute pipeline stability and eliminating ingestion downtime.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="project-entry mb-5 border-start border-2 vs-accent-line ps-4">
                    <div class="d-flex justify-content-between align-items-baseline flex-wrap mb-2">
                        <h3 class="h4 fw-bold m-0 vs-type">Automated Data Validation & Ingestion Utility</h3>
                        <span class="vs-comment font-monospace small">// C# • .NET Core • Data Automation • I/O Optimization</span>
                    </div>

                    <p class="vs-text my-3 lh-lg">
                        A standalone C# automation utility that streamlines corporate client onboarding by eliminating manual file verification, extracting structural identity keys, and executing dynamic file-system routing rules.
                    </p>

                    <div class="row pt-2">
                        <div class="col-md-6 mb-3">
                            <h4 class="h6 text-uppercase fw-bold vs-keyword small tracking-wide mb-2">The Workflow</h4>
                            <p class="vs-text small lh-base">
                                Programmatically extracts unique identity keys from raw client media, streams associated CSV manifests to execute lookups, and automatically mutates file nomenclature (e.g., prepending <code class="small vs-code-inline">LPR_</code>) to govern downstream compiler behavior.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-md-6 mb-3">
                            <h4 class="h6 text-uppercase fw-bold vs-keyword small tracking-wide mb-2">Business Impact</h4>
                            <p class="vs-text small lh-base">
                                Replaced a highly manual, error-prone monthly auditing process with a multi-threaded console application. Reduced processing cycles from hours to seconds, eliminated keying risks, and integrated an exception-logging module to isolate data anomalies instantly.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </details>
    </section>

    <hr class="vs-hr my-5" />

    <footer class="text-center py-4 mt-5">
        <p class="vs-comment font-monospace mb-3">// Let's connect.</p>
        <div class="d-flex justify-content-center gap-4">
            <a href="https://github.com/yourusername" target="_blank" class="vs-keyword text-decoration-none fw-bold">GitHub</a>
            <a href="https://linkedin.com/in/yourusername" target="_blank" class="vs-type text-decoration-none fw-bold">LinkedIn</a>
            <a href="mailto:youremail@example.com" class="vs-string text-decoration-none fw-bold">Email</a>
        </div>
    </footer>

</div>